[3] Philippines (Western Visayas)
Date: Wed 26 May 2010
Source: The News Today [edited]
<http://www.thenewstoday.info/2010/05/26/ipho.verifies.dengue.outbreak.in.tubungan.town.html>


A team from the Epidemiologic Surveillance Unit (ESU) of Iloilo
Provincial Health Office (IPHO) visited Barangay [neighborhood]
Cadapdap of this town yesterday [25 May 2010] to check the status of
15 suspected dengue cases initially reported from the said barangay.
According to IPHO assistant chief Maria Socorro Quinon, once her team
confirms that those cases are positive, it means the area has a dengue
outbreak. "An area with highest number of reported dengue cases is not
a good indication," she stressed.

Dengue is transmitted by _Aedes aegypti_ and _Aedes albopictus_
mosquitoes. These are day-biting mosquitoes that breed in clear,
stagnant [not flowing] waters.

A total of 4 deaths were already recorded in Iloilo province from
January [2010] up to the present. Casualties came from the towns of
Guimbal, Oton, Pototan, and one component of the city of Passi. Last
year from 1 Jan-10 Jun [2009], a total of 286 dengue cases were
recorded by the IPHO.

So far, Quinon said that they are expecting the number of dengue cases
will increase during rainy season. June is considered the month of the
rainy season; thus, the IPHO advised the public to clean their
surroundings and to properly dispose of tin cans, empty bottles, used
tires, and other containers that are potential breeding areas of
dengue [virus]-carrying mosquitoes.

In Western Visayas region, the Department of Health 6 (DOH-6) has so
far recorded a total of 1311 cases [4 times the Jan.-June 2009 total]
-- with 7 deaths -- from January to May 8 this year [2010]. Negros
Occidental has the highest number of recorded cases at 380 with 2
deaths, followed by Bacolod City with 266 cases. Iloilo Province has
231 cases with 4 deaths, while Iloilo City has 126 cases. There were
194 cases in Capiz, 79 in Aklan, with one death, 16 in Guimaras, and
12 in Antique.

[Buline: Montesa Grino-Caoyonan]

--
